					</section>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Who makes FOSS ?</h2>
					
					<ul>
						<li class="fragment">Multiple Users as Co-Developers for a collaborative effort</li>
						<li class="fragment">Users share their Functional and Technical Knowledge</li>
						<li class="fragment">Bugs are kept open and visible</li>
						<li class="fragment">Easy and Fast bug fixing</li>
					</ul>
						
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>What can FOSS do ?</h2>
					<ul>
						<li class="fragment">Can reuse,modify,build and integrate software based on the system available</li>
						<li class="fragment">Can customize and modify the software according to our needs</li>
						<li class="fragment">Hence , save a lot of money and give competitive advantage to the organisation</li>
						
					</ul>
				</section>

